entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: hi i am ellie thanks for coming in today i was created to talk to people in a safe and secure environment i am not a therapist but i am here to learn about people and would love to learn about you i will ask a few questions to get us started and please feel free to tell me anything your answers are totally confidential are you ok with this

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yes

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: okay so how are you doing today

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i am not bad i am a little tired but okay

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good where are you from originally

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: from saint louis missouri

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: really

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: yep

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i see do you consider yourself more shy or outgoing

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i guess i am kinda shy it depends on the people and the environment i guess

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: i understand sometimes when i am feeling tense i turn on the fish tank screensaver hey i know it is not hawaii but it is the best i have got what do you do to relax

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: play guitar listen to some music talk to friends

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: cool how are you at controlling your temper

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i would say i am pretty good at controlling my temper i am not the type of guy that gets angry really easily

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is good when was the last time you argued with someone and what was it about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: probably with my girlfriend over something silly i can not even remember

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is something you feel guilty about

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: do not know i do not think i am really guilty about anything i try to avoid being guilty

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: h who is someone that is been a positive influence in your life

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i guess most of my friends they are always there to support me and encourage me and help me so

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: that is so good to hear how easy is it for you to get a good night is sleep

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: say pretty easy every once in awhile there is a night i can not sleep but it is pretty rare

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what are you like when you do not sleep well

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just tired groggy i guess my mind is unfocused and day goes by heck of a lot longer

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how have you been feeling lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: pretty good not really much to say

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you noticed any changes in your behavior or thoughts lately

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: maybe a little bit more depressed cause i am away from most of my friends and family but nothing unmanageable

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: how do you cope with them

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: just try to talk to em when i can think about something else think about happy times

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you ever been diagnosed with ptsd

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: have you been diagnosed with depression

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: no

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: tell me about the last time you felt really happy

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i guess on the drive out here cause it was such a new experience and so exhilarating

entries.speaker: ellie
entries.text: what is one of your most memorable experiences

entries.speaker: participant
entries.text: i think graduating college cause i was really proud of myself and really looking forward to the future
